sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>Web Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant S3 as S3 Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Runtime as Runtime Image Pod<br/>Elyra Pipeline Step

    %% Flow 1: User Access
    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Notebook
        User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/lab<br/>Session Cookie
        Router->>OAuth: Forward HTTPS Request<br/>TLS 1.2+
        OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OpenShift OAuth Token<br/>RequestAuthentication
        OAuth->>Jupyter: Proxy to JupyterLab<br/>HTTP (no token, trusted pod network)
        Jupyter-->>OAuth: JupyterLab UI HTML
        OAuth-->>Router: Response
        Router-->>User: Encrypted Response
    end

    %% Flow 2: Notebook Operations
    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Jupyter,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Notebook Executes oc Commands
        User->>Jupyter: Execute cell with `oc get pods`
        Jupyter->>K8sAPI: GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/pods<br/>Bearer: ServiceAccount Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
        K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: Pod List JSON
        Jupyter-->>User: Display results in notebook
    end

    %% Flow 3: Data Access
    rect rgb(255, 250, 230)
        Note over Jupyter,S3: Flow 3: Notebook Reads/Writes Data to S3
        User->>Jupyter: Run cell: boto3.client('s3').get_object(...)
        Jupyter->>S3: GET /bucket/dataset.csv<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth (from secret)<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        S3-->>Jupyter: Dataset CSV
        Jupyter-->>User: Load into pandas DataFrame

        User->>Jupyter: Run cell: df.to_parquet('s3://...')
        Jupyter->>S3: PUT /bucket/output.parquet<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        S3-->>Jupyter: 200 OK
        Jupyter-->>User: Success message
    end

    %% Flow 4: Pipeline Execution
    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Runtime: Flow 4: Elyra Pipeline Execution (Runtime Image)
        User->>Jupyter: Submit Elyra pipeline to KFP
        Jupyter->>KFP: POST /apis/v1beta1/pipelines<br/>Bearer Token<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        KFP-->>Jupyter: Pipeline Run ID

        KFP->>Runtime: Create Pod with Runtime Image<br/>K8s Pod Spec
        Runtime->>S3: GET /bucket/input-notebook.ipynb<br/>AWS SigV4<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        S3-->>Runtime: Notebook file
        Runtime->>Runtime: Execute via papermill<br/>python3 -m papermill
        Runtime->>S3: PUT /bucket/output-artifacts.tar.gz<br/>AWS SigV4<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        S3-->>Runtime: 200 OK
        Runtime-->>KFP: Pipeline step complete
        KFP-->>User: Pipeline status update
    end

    %% Flow 5: Package Installation
    rect rgb(250, 250, 250)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 5: Install Additional Packages
        User->>Jupyter: Run cell: !pip install scikit-image
        Jupyter->>PyPI: GET /simple/scikit-image/<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package metadata + wheel
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Install to /opt/app-root/lib/python3.9/site-packages
        Jupyter-->>User: Successfully installed
    end
